description:
&lt;p&gt;Various posts available - Full time (or part time may be considered)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Are you interested in working in busy, dynamic and friendly Outpatient Departments delivering a 7 day service across multiple specialities.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for motivated and flexible Band 2 Nursing Assistants to join our Outpatients teams predominantly to work in main Outpatients at our Wansbeck or North Tyneside Hospitals.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to support trauma and orthopaedics clinics based at our Northumbria Specialist Emergency Care Hospital at Cramlington, therefore being a car driver&#39;s is essential.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to be flexible and work within other Outpatient areas within each of the hospitals across all speciality&#39;s&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We will provide a supportive learning environment and encourage you with your personal and professional development.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Experience or an interest in out patients or clinics would be beneficial.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Essential:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Understanding of patients basic needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous care experience preferably in a healthcare setting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Desirable:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NVQ Level 2 in direct care/health/health and social care&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;em&gt;PLEASE NOTE THAT WE RESERVE THE RIGHT TO CLOSE VACANCIES PRIOR TO THE ADVERTISED CLOSING DATE WHEN WE ARE IN RECEIPT OF SUFFICIENT APPLICATIONS&lt;/em&gt;&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Christine Hart Department Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address Christine.hart@nhct.nhs.uk&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number 0344 811 8111 Ext 32644&lt;/p&gt;
